history.content: I found 16B to be a lot of work but 134 almost take no time (I took 70 before that so it might be different for you).

Hello there. I'm a second year intended CS and I'm picking out classes soon and I wanted to get some feedback on this schedule: Stat134, EE16B, IEOR 135, and either a decal/desinv24/engin 25. I've taken CS 61A/B, Math 1A/B, and currently in EE16A and CS 61C. 

For those who have taken EE16B before taking CS 70, do you think 16B prepared you for 70 in any way, whether that be getting slightly more familiar with proofs or "developing mathematical maturity"?

I'm considering taking Stat 134 to prepare for the stats portion of CS 70(sounds ridiculous to take an upper div to prepare for a lower div, but I really need to good grade in 70 to declare CS) while using the class as a prereq for the IEOR minor. What was the workload like for Stat 134 and EE16B @ those who took either or both? Thanks!
history.subject: Stat 134 and EE16B
